Apis.Details.Subscribe.test.description:
Create an Application and subscribe this API to that Application.
                                                An application is a logical collection of APIs.
                                                Applications allow you to use a single access token to invoke a collection
                                                of APIs and to subscribe to one API multiple times with different SLA levels.
                                                The DefaultApplication is pre-created and allows unlimited access by default.

The application can use the following grant types to generate

Shared.AppsAndKeys.Tokens.when.you.gener: When you generate access tokens to APIs protected by scope/s, you can select the scope/s and then generate the token for it. Scopes enable fine-grained access control to API resources based on user roles. You define scopes to an API resource. When a user invokes the API, his/her OAuth 2 bearer token cannot grant access to any API resource beyond its associated scopes.
Shared.AppsAndKeys.Tokens.apikey.set.val: You can set an expiration period to determine the validity period of the token after generation. Set this as -1 to ensure that the apikey never expires.
